{"word":"μονογενής","slug":"μονογενής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>μονογενής, ές</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:μόνος\">μόνος</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:γένος\">γένος</a></el> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:γίνομαι\">γίνομαι</a></el>] ‘being the only one of a kind’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> in context <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ freq.\">freq.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> sense of strong personal attachment <b>sole, only <a href='B:490 7:12'>Lk 7:12</a>; <a href='B:490 8:42'>8:42</a>; <a href='B:490 9:38'>9:38</a>; <a href='B:500 1:14'>J 1:14</a>; <a href='B:500 3:16'>3:16</a>; <a href='B:650 11:17'>Hb 11:17</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> focus on distinctiveness, <b>unique <a href='B:500 1:18'>J 1:18</a></b> (if the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ rdg.\">rdg.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὁ\">ὁ</a> μονογενὴς <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:υἱός\">υἱός</a></el> the unique son is accepted); <b><a href='B:500 3:18'>3:18</a>; <a href='B:690 4:9'>1 J 4:9</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:μονή\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:μόνον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}